properties.theft_detail: Some one stole my bike from the bike rack outside Habit coffee shop
Someone stole the front wheel off my bicycle. The bike was locked to a pole inside the parking area behind my apartment building.

Hardtail Mountain bike locked with new expensive chain lock. I was away from bike for 20 minutes. When I came back, the lock was snapped, on the ground. The bike was gone. Police were not interested in following up, because of how common a problem it was.

Filed a report to Campus security who filed it onto police.
They cut my Kryptonite cable and stole the entire front end of my mountain bike (wheel, suspension fork, handlebars along with all the shifters, etc.). Approx. value: $800.
Don't bring your nice bike to UVic unless locking in a locker.
Bikes left in backyard, under sheltered part of house. 3 bikes were stolen.
Back tire wasn't locked, front tire was. They stole the back tire
Accidentally left bike unlocked for 5 mins when I ran into Canadian Tire to get batteries because my bike lights were dead.

I was waiting to pay my check at a nearby cafe, and within the 20 seconds it took to sign the receipt and gather my belongings, our cable lock was cut and our 2 road bikes (cannondale synapse and specialized allez) were stolen.  They were never more than 20 feet from us, but it happened so fast.
Left my bike locked outside on my front porch. Came outside to find the cable lock was snipped and the bike was gone.
Bicycle stolen from residential garage.

Bike left in basement of small apartment building (11 units - everyone knows everyone else). Entrance door to building accessible only with key. No facilities or even exposed pipes, etc., for locking a bike to in the basement. 

Bike parked there after PM commute home. Next AM bike was missing.
bike helmet and light was stolen
locked to a parking meter. went for dinner.. came out and it was gone.

It's a town cruiser Marin, flat handle bars, black fenders, metal pannier on the back with a black retractable basket attached to it, a silver bell made in the Netherlands on the left hand side handle bar, the frame is a straight high bar with a slight curve to it, and it's a grey/purple colour.

The bike racks in front of the Downsview TTC Station were full so I decided to place my bike on a light post just outside of a used car dealership and at the time was using a very bad lock. Luckily the bike was only $100. Came back at around 5:30 in the afternoon to find the bike gone.
Locked my Charge Zester against a large stop sign in front of Target store on Coleman Ave, near San Jose airport. Went into store for about 20 minutes, bike was gone on my return.
Seat and seatpost stolen from Dahon Helios folding bike, parked against a fence in rear of parking lot behind 1762 Technology Dr, San Jose. Incident was witnessed from office in building.
Bike was left in van overnight and van was broken into
while the CSB bike rack is a popular and  busy bike lockup mon-fri, on the weekend it is very quiet and a perfect place for someone to steal a bike undetected
My bike and two others taken from outdoor bike rack at the commuter rail station/bus loop.
3 bikes stolen from a shed, only accessible from inside the febced yard. All bikes were locked to the wall of the shed.
Bike saddle bag stolen (multi-tool, levers, tube) along with frame pump.
brompton foldable bike in light and dark green color, 6 speeds
Bike was stolen from  a flimsy bike rack inside a locked room in a parkade with 2 gates.

The theft happened at the Glenn Alps parking lot, at the trailhead to Flattop Mountain. I thought my bike was safe just because that's a place where people go hiking. When I returned from my hike, the front wheel was gone. Easy to steal since the cable lock only passed through frame and back wheel.
All of my lights (some working, some totally dead)
parking sign was dismantled and slipped up through my ulock.

bike was locked for less than one hour at a busy area of Olympic Village Plaza.  I had my U lock with me, but the racks were too busy to find a place where it would fit.  I had to use my cable instead.  :(

Posting for coworker: State Bike Co matte black 55cm with silver wheels and bar tape on bull horn style bars. Rear fender. Bike was a delivery drivers bike leaned against jimmy johns store front window.

I had my bike locked to the bike rack on my car, parked in my underground parking (supposedly secure) spot. The bike was stolen off the bike rack early Wednesday morning (3am) there was video surveillance. I was not aware anything was amiss until a day later when I went to drive to work.

My bike had been locked to my front railing for nearly four years. I went out for a run at 9:30 a.m. And the bike was gone when I returned at 11. Sawed through Kryptonite u-lock. Pinhead locking screws throughout so I rarely used my cable. It was a 2010 GT Traffic 3.0 and was my main mode of transpo
stolen from a locked bike room in the underground parking of my building.  Thieves recorded on CCTV
Dark green mountain bike that was given to me by a friend who moved
It wasn't locked because it was on a second-storey balcony. It had been taken out of storage and put on the balcony. A week later, it was gone.
Bike was not successfully stolen. Residents of the apartment building scared away the thief.
Lights and small toolbag under saddle got stolen off 2 bikes (same incident).

Half my bike was missing. He dropped the forks out after loosening the headset, then cut the cables and left with handlebars, front forks and tire and all the attached components. Replacement value:My time and $503.
my daughter left her bike at her elementary school bike rack within the school ground and it got stolen during the day

In the early morning hours of Tuesday, December 9, my Nishiki bicycle, was stolen for our garden shed. The theft was discovered at 5 am. There were two other older model bikes, remaining in the shed. The bicycle is described as a blue Nishiki, Eclipse.

Bike was parked outside of entry to basement suite on patio. Only access to patio is around the side of the house along the private driveway. It was stolen in the middle of the night, sometime when I parked it at 9 pm on Sunday night and 8 am on Monday morning when I went to use it.
